---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of service | HoundStack"
  description="The HoundStack terms of service: the agreement covering accounts, pricing by active clients, acceptable use, data ownership, and cancellation."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Terms of service</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated July 6, 2026. Draft pending legal review.</p>

      <h2>The agreement</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are an agreement between your business and HoundStack covering use of the
        HoundStack product and this website. Creating an account means you accept them on behalf
        of your business.
      </p>

      <h2>Accounts and pricing</h2>
      <p>
        Plans are priced by tier as published on the <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a>. Each
        tier includes an allowance of active employees; an active employee is anyone with a login
        used at least once in the billing period, in any role. Additional active employees beyond
        the allowance are billed at a flat $10 per month each, shown in the billing dashboard as
        incurred. New accounts receive a 60 day free trial of the Launch plan, time based and not
        contingent on usage. Yearly billing receives a 15% discount on the plan price. Plan
        changes are prorated within the billing period.
      </p>

      <h2>Your data</h2>
      <p>
        The business data you enter belongs to you. You can export it in one click at any time,
        including after cancellation for a reasonable wind down period. We claim no ownership of
        your client lists, records, or photos, and we do not sell them.
      </p>

      <h2>Payments</h2>
      <p>
        Payment processing runs on your own Stripe account under Stripe's terms. HoundStack takes
        no percentage of your payment volume. Subscription fees for HoundStack itself are billed
        monthly.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        Use the product to run your business, not to break the law, spam, attempt unauthorized
        access to other accounts, or resell the service without an agreement. SMS features must be
        used in compliance with applicable messaging regulations, including obtaining consent to
        text your clients.
      </p>

      <h2>Availability and support</h2>
      <p>
        We work to keep the service available and to fix real problems quickly, and the service is
        provided as is without a formal uptime guarantee on standard plans. Offline features in
        the mobile app are designed to keep field work running during connectivity gaps.
      </p>

      <h2>Cancellation</h2>
      <p>
        You can cancel at any time. Access continues through the end of the paid period, your data
        remains exportable, and we do not do exit fees or retention phone gauntlets.
      </p>

      <h2>Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the extent permitted by law, HoundStack's liability is limited to the amount you paid
        for the service in the twelve months before a claim. Neither party is liable for indirect
        or consequential damages.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        If these terms change materially, account owners will be notified by email before the
        change takes effect. Continued use after notice means acceptance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: clamp(40px, 6vw, 72px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(48px, 6vw, 80px);
  }
</style>
